{"lemma":"سَبِيلٌ","slug":"سَبِيلٌ","root":"س.ب.ل","root_slug":"س-ب-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ب-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَبِيل","root":"سبل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":176},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18820"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%84%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"way, path, road"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"manner, method"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ways and means"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"kinship"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"necessary connection"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"distribution of water"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"public fountain"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"blame","examples":[{"text":"إِنَّمَا السَّبِيلُ عَلَى الَّذِينَ يَظْلِمُونَ النَّاسَ وَيَبْغُونَ فِي الْأَرْضِ بِغَيْرِ الْحَقِّ ۚ أُولَٰئِكَ لَهُمْ عَذَابٌ أَلِيمٌ","english":"The blame is only against the ones who wrong the people and tyrannize upon the earth without right. Those will have a painful punishment."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root س ب ل (s b l). Given the frequent religious usage of the word, there is some semantic interference of the Classical Syriac ܫܒܝܠܐ (šəbīlā). Cognate to Aramaic שְׁבִילׇא (šəḇīlā), Hebrew שְׁבִיל (šəḇī́l, “trail, path”)."},"ipa":["/sa.biːl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18820","headword_ar":"سَبِيلٌ","root":"sbl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A way, road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"path;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is open,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conspicuous, thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) and Er-Rághib adds,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wherein is easiness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiylapN","text_ar":"سَبِيلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (Ibn- 'Abbád, K:) the former is masc. and fem.; (S, M, Mgh, Msb, K;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zuqaAqN","text_ar":"زُقَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) made fem. by the people of El-Hijáz, and masc. by Temeem; (Akh, S voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zuqaAqN","text_ar":"زُقَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) but mostly fem.; (IAth, TA;) in the Kur it is made masc. in vii. 143, and fem. in xii. 108: (S, M, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subulN","text_ar":"سُبُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) or, accord. to ISk, it has this pl. when masc., and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subuwlN","text_ar":"سُبُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunuwqN","text_ar":"عُنُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"when fem., (Msb, [but this distinction and the latter pl. are both strange,]) and it has also as a pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asobilapN","text_ar":"اَسْبِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) In the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa EalaY A@ll~`hi qaSodu Als~abiyli","text_ar":"وَ عَلَى ا@للّٰهِ قَصْدُ السَّبِيلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And upon God it rests to show the right way"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qSd","text_ar":"قصد"},{"kind":"text","text":")], (M, K,) in the Kur [xvi. 9], (M,) it is used as a gen. n., because it is added,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa minohaA jaAy^irN","text_ar":"وَ مِنْهَا جَايِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu Als~abiyli","text_ar":"اِبْنُ السَّبِيلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The son of the road;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he whom the road has brought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as it were"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brought forth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IB;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the wayfarer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"traveller:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he who travels much"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"often:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the traveller who is far from his place of abode:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib:) as used in the verse of the Kur, (M, Mgh, Msb,) ix, 60, (M,) it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the person to whom the way has become cut short"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that he is unable to continue his journey"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (M, K;) to which has been added,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who desires to return to his country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"town, and finds not what will suffice him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the traveller who is cut off from his property:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the person who desires to go to a country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"town, other than his own, for a necessary affair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to Ibn-'Arafeh,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the guest who has become disabled from proceeding in his journey, his means having failed him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"to such should be given as much as will suffice him to his home. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqoTaEuwna Als~abiyla","text_ar":"تَقْطَعُونَ السَّبِيلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xxix. 28], means (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And ye cut off"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the way of offspring"},{"kind":"text","text":"[by your unnatural practices]: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and ye oppose yourselves to men in the roads"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"road"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the purpose of that which is excessively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enormously, foul"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abominable."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiylu","text_ar":"سَبِيلُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cause, of God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of religion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the way whereby one seeks approach to God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"advancement in his favour."},{"kind":"text","text":"] It is said in the Kur [ii. 191],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa A^anofiquwA fiY sabiyli A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"وَ اَنْفِقُوا فِى سَبِيلِ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And expend ye in warring against unbelievers"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in every good work commanded by God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) such being of the ways [that lead] to God: (M:) mostly used in relation to warring against unbelievers and the like. (M, K.) And in the same, iii. 163,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@l~a*iyna qutiluwA","text_ar":"ا@لَّذِينَ قُتِلُوا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY sabiyli A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"فِى سَبِيلِ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Who have been slain in the cause of God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of his religion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the sake of the religion of God."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEala DayoEatahu fiY sabiyli A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"جَعَلَ ضَيْعَتَهُ فِى سَبِيلِ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made his estate to have its profit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"revenue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"usufruct, employed in the cause of God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of religion"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiylN","text_ar":"سَبِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A means of access; a connexion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tie:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the saying, in the Kur [xxv. 29],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA layotaniY A@t~axa*otu maEa A@lr~asuwli sabiylFA","text_ar":"يَا لَيْتَنِى ا@تَّخَذْتُ مَعَ ا@لرَّسُولِ سَبِيلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O would that I had obtained, with the Apostle, a means of access"},{"kind":"text","text":"to Paradise]: (S, Msb, TA:) thus it has been explained: (TA:) or the meaning is, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O would that I had taken, with the Apostle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a way to safety:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the way of truth. (Bd.) ―         -b6-  [Also, in the present day, applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A public drinking-fountain."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","M","K","Mgh","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}